This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual object segmentation. It may also belong to the Sound (cs.SD) and Sound and Music Computing (cs.SI) sub-categories as it deals with sound source separation. Additionally, it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it uses neural networks for learning. Finally, it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with both visual and audio data.
